image.altText: A horse looks into a camera.

props.synopsis: The RSPCA is investigating after three emaciated thoroughbred horses were found on a property in southern Tasmania — animals which were once owned by Tasmania's former attorney-general Vanessa Goodwin.

title.children: Heartbreak, anger on social media over horses once owned by former Tasmanian attorney-general

image.altText: Rebecca White election night March 23, 2024

props.synopsis: After a third straight election defeat, Rebecca White's decision to step down as Tasmanian Labor party leader hardly came as a surprise.

title.children: White says resigning was by choice, but was conceding the Tasmanian election her call?

image.altText: Julian Assange looks to the camera as he is photographed from behind glass with graffiti etched into it. His grey hair is back.

props.synopsis: WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange has been handed a legal lifeline by the High Court in London where he is trying to appeal his extradition to the United States.

title.children: Julian Assange handed extradition lifeline in court, US told not to seek death penalty

image.altText: A helicopter flies over the scene of the Francis Scott Key Bridge collapse in Baltimore shows  part of a bridge borken over ship

props.synopsis: Six construction workers who were on a bridge in Baltimore remain missing after a container ship crashed into it and caused it to collapse into a river, authorities in the north-eastern US city say.

title.children: Search on for survivors in Baltimore bridge collapse after container ship crashes into pylon

image.altText: Luke Dorsett was killed on the Thunder River Rapids ride at Dreamworld.

props.synopsis: Luke Dorsett's mother has known for years that his final actions saved the life of his 12-year-old niece. Today his bravery has been nationally recognised, alongside several bystanders who rushed to help.

title.children: Dreamworld victim's heroic final act recognised with bravery award seven years after his death

image.altText: A woman with blonde hair and pink blazer speaks into press microphones

props.synopsis: After three election defeats, Rebecca White resigns as Tasmanian Labor leader. It could prompt a battle between the party's left and right factions to decide on the next leader.

title.children: 'Time for me to move on': Rebecca White resigns as Tasmanian Labor leader

image.altText: Jeremy Rockliff walks through a crowded room and cameras film him.

props.synopsis: While Jeremy Rockliff's Liberals won more seats than Labor at Tasmania's election, the party won't reach majority. Here's how minority governments are formed, and how they've worked in the past.

title.children: Tasmania has elected a hung parliament. Here's what that means

image.altText: A satellite image from 2014 next to one from 2023 showing how much tree growth there has been in that time.

props.synopsis: Researchers find some of the nation's biggest polluters are meeting their emissions obligations using carbon credits that have not actually resulted in emissions reductions.

title.children: Biggest polluters meeting emissions rules using credits that did not reduce CO2, researchers find

image.altText: A Coles and Woolworths reward card

props.synopsis: There are calls for greater regulation of the data collected by Coles and Woolworths from the millions of transactions that happen in their stores every week.

title.children: How using a supermarket rewards card could be giving Coles and Woolworths more power

image.altText: A young man with short hair walks out of a court building.

props.synopsis: Hobart Hurricanes player Nikhil Chaudhary, 27, is accused of sexually assaulting a woman in North Queensland in 2021.

title.children: Hobart Hurricanes cricketer Nikhil Chaudhary stands trial for rape in Townsville

image.altText: A green field, surrounded by cows.

props.synopsis: A slice of what was Australia's largest dairy farm in Tasmania's fertile north-west has been purchased by a Melbourne-based management fund as part of a 10,000 dairy cow goal.

title.children: Tasmanian farm the size of Gibraltar sells for $15m in 'good deal' for management fund

image.altText: Andrew Giles sits alongside Mark Butler in the House of Representatives

props.synopsis: Andrew Giles has come a long way from his days as a refugee lawyer. Now Australia's immigration minister, he's suddenly found himself in a rush to bolster the federal government's powers to deport people.

title.children: Andrew Giles looked like someone waiting for a root canal as he gained extraordinary powers

image.altText: Video of dappled sunlight shining through giant underwater kelp forest

props.synopsis: Tucked away in a picturesque bay on the Tasman Peninsula is a precious underwater field of giant kelp that's thriving thanks to a team of determined scientists.

title.children: In this picturesque Tasmanian bay, marine scientists are bringing a once-lost habitat back to life

image.altText: Two Liberal Party advertisements side-by-side.

props.synopsis: Former Tasmanian and Victorian Liberal Party boss Sam McQuestin is fined $40,000 after a court rules federal election ads printed in a regional newspaper were in breach of laws because the authorisation was too small and difficult to read.

title.children: Former Tasmanian and Victorian Liberal Party boss fined $40k

image.altText: A Qantas plane can be seen on the tarmac at Sydney Airport as a silhouetted man walks past a window inside the terminal.

props.synopsis: Australian airlines have been called out recently over high prices but some industry insiders say the real problem within the industry is the airports.

title.children: 'Cost us more than fuel': Rex executive lashes airports over fees that can drive up prices

image.altText: People sit behind a desk with their hand raised in a vote

props.synopsis: Washington's decision to allow a vote at the United Nations Security Council that Israel did not want indicates a new low between the United States and Israel.

title.children: A shock vote at the UN and a fit of pique by Bibi reveals the new low in American-Israeli relations

image.altText: Two police cars and one ambulance at the end of the road next to the sea

title.children: Three people found dead after fishing boat capsizes near Port Lincoln

image.altText: Exterior of building with Live Better signage and garden

props.synopsis: The 28-year-old died five days after receiving burns to up to 40 per cent of her body while being bathed by disability carers. The Federal Court has heard the training and assessment of staff were "inadequate".

title.children: Non-verbal woman died after suffering burns in bathwater that reached 60 degrees, court told

image.altText: Man in a navy suit with a light blue tie.

props.synopsis: The former chief of staff to ex-Liberal MP Craig Kelly was found guilty earlier this year of indecent assault against four of his female staff members, with two describing the long-term impacts of the experience.

title.children: Woman abused by former Craig Kelly staffer tells court she 'will never feel completely safe again'

image.altText: A woman and young man laying flowers beside a road

props.synopsis: The wife and the stepson of two truck drivers killed in a horrific crash at Maryborough say their families will support each other and are "in this together", during a meeting on the roadside where their loved ones died.

image.altText: Brahman cattle looking over the rails of a truck.

props.synopsis: More than 100 Australian cattle have died on a live export ship to Indonesia — likely one of the highest mortality rates ever reported on an Australian livestock shipment.

title.children: More than 100 cattle die at sea in export from Australia to Indonesia

image.altText: A line of people boarding an ADF aircraft on an airstrip in a remote community.

title.children: Land council slams 'horror' evacuations of flood-hit Borroloola

image.altText: Image shows congestion and traffic delays. You can see cars, grey road on a gloomy day.

props.synopsis: The federal government will water down proposed carbon emissions laws for vehicles, as it seeks to appease car makers who feared it would push up the price of some cars by thousands of dollars.

title.children: Carbon emissions limits for cars weakened amid opposition's 'ute tax' campaign

image.altText: truck v train 1

props.synopsis: The 29-year-old Victorian is facing a charge of dangerous driving over the incident in February, which was filmed and widely shared online.

title.children: Truck driver charged after hair-raising close call with freight train

image.altText: Swans players

props.synopsis: Sydney Swans AFLW players Alexia Hamilton and Paige Sheppard have been handed a two-game ban and expressed remorse after being found guilty of drug possession.

title.children: Sydney Swans AFLW players banned for two matches after drug charges

image.altText: Tamara Oudyn sits at the newsdesk, with a film of distortion covering her face.

props.synopsis: An estimated 4.9 million Australians battle through the debilitating pain of migraines. But despite estimates the condition costs the national economy billions each year, a leading researcher says there's far from enough funding or support.

title.children: If I'm getting a migraine while reading the news, my face is a dead giveaway

image.altText: high courtF1

props.synopsis: The federal government has introduced legislation to parliament which would make it easier to deport non-citizens. This is how it would work.

title.children: The government's last-minute migration bill has reached the Senate. Here's what's in it.

image.altText: A young man with short hair walks out of a court building.

props.synopsis: Hobart Hurricanes player Nikhil Chaudhary, 27, is accused of sexually assaulting a woman in North Queensland in 2021.

title.children: Big Bash cricketer stands trial for allegedly raping woman outside nightclub

image.altText: Karen Payne in Sydney sitting at a park bench looking into the distance.

props.synopsis: Two federal ombudsmen have joined forces to launch a scathing review of the Australian Tax Office and call on government agencies to act more fairly when they chase people for debts.

title.children: 'You can't have a one size fits all': ATO told it's being unfair to taxpayers it's chasing for old debts

image.altText: A smoldering log within the fire zone of the Waroona Bushfire.

props.synopsis: The alert level for a bushfire burning south of Perth is downgraded to 'watch and act', after a flare up on Tuesday afternoon prompted authorities to briefly reissue an emergency alert.

title.children: Fire south of Perth eases after flare up as authorities warn of risks in 'incredibly dry' bush

image.altText: People stand on the far side of a river bank, looking cold on a grey day as the brown water cuts off a road.

title.children: Record outback rains could move south this Easter

image.altText: hands typing on a computer keyboard.

props.synopsis: The Coalition is pressing the federal government to hit China with sanctions after Australia joined with the United States, the United Kingdom and New Zealand to accuse Beijing of orchestrating a sweeping campaign of cyber espionage.

title.children: Coalition calls for sanctions against China after Beijing accused of cyber espionage in US and UK

image.altText: Two  women walk past the Reserve Bank of Australia headquarters, with the building's name prominent in the background.

props.synopsis: Despite the brutal round of interest rate hikes, people are still holding onto their jobs — and the unpredictable nature of the real world is making a mockery of economics textbooks. Is it a miracle, or have we arrived at a point where unemployment and inflation can subside together?

title.children: Deal with the devil: Why central banks want you out of work

image.altText: A silver Brompton bicycle stands against a white wall.

props.synopsis: The 61-year-old, widely credited for helping bring Formula 1 racing to Singapore in 2008, now faces a total of 35 charges, including improperly receiving a UK-made folding bicycle, bottles of whisky and golf clubs worth more than $21,000.

title.children: Former transport minister who helped bring F1 to Singapore accused of improperly receiving bicycle

image.altText: A yellow boat in the ocean with two people standing at the front

props.synopsis: Police say one person has died and two people are still missing after a fishing boat with five people onboard capsized near Port Lincoln yesterday. A man and a youth were found on a reef nearby and are being treated in hospital.

title.children: One person found dead, search continues for two missing after fishing boat capsizes in South Australian waters
